Fazil Iskander Award winners named
The awards were presented to the winners of the Fazil Iskander Award.
The award ceremony was held at the Central House of Literature in Moscow.
In the "Prose" category, the winner was Kantha Ibragimov, the novel "Stigal".
The novel "Stigal" begins as the diary of a cancer patient and turns into an epic work by the end.
In the "Poetry" category - Vyacheslav Shapovalov, the book of poems "Eurasian".
"Best Screenplay" is a work by Sergei Dmitrenko based on the stories told by Fazil Iskander in the book "Sandro from Chegemen".
In the nomination "Chegem heights" - Auren Habichev, the cycle of stories "My Great Nothing".
Besides the main competition, special diplomas were awarded to Elena Nesterina for the story "Eternal happiness!" and Lyudmila Vyazmitinova for the book of poems "Monthessels", TASS reports.
Fazil Iskander (1929-2016) was born in Sukhum.
In 1954 he graduated from the Literary Institute.
His first collections of poetry - "Mountain Paths" (1957), "The Goodness of the Earth" (1959), "Green Rain" (1960) - received recognition from critics and readers.
He became famous for his novel "The Constellation of the Cozlotura" (1966).
The most famous novel by Iskander is "Sandro from Chegem".
