The Ministry of Finance predicts a weakening of the rate to 73.9 rubles per dollar by 2031-2035.
The Russian Ministry of Finance predicts a gradual weakening of the ruble to 73.9 rubles per US dollar in the period up to 2036.
The agency also forecasts a stabilization of world oil prices in the range of $40-50 per barrel during this period.
This is stated in the "Budget forecast of the Russian Federation until 2036" on the budget system portal.
According to the forecast of the Ministry of Finance of the Russian Federation, the ruble to the US dollar in the period 2021-2025 will be 66.4 rubles / dollar, in 2026-2030 - 71.1 rubles / dollars, and in the period 2031-2035 - 73.9 rubles / dollars.
In addition, according to the Russian department, with a high probability, the price of oil on the medium and long-term horizon stabilizes in the range of 40-45 dollars per barrel at constant prices.
Urals oil, according to the Ministry of Finance, will cost $55.2 per barrel in the period 2021-2025, $52.2 per barrel in 2026-2030 and $54.9 per barrel in the period 2031-2035.
