Sirius students discussed nature-like technology with scientists
The students of the educational center "Sirius" in Sochi, participants of the School of Agrobiology and Plant Genetics, attended a lecture by scientists of the national research center "Kurchatov Institute".
The researchers' speech was held as part of the program of the Global International Forum of Convergent and Nature-like Technologies, organized in Sochi on behalf of Russian President Vladimir Putin, according to the website of the educational center on September 29.
The lecture was opened by the documentary film "Kurchatov's Codes", during which the president of the Kurchatov Institute, correspondent member of the Russian Academy of Sciences, Mikhail Kovalchuk, spoke about global challenges as the driving force of the development of civilization.
The scientist's lecture is published on the website of "Sirius".
The students learned that modern technology requires a huge amount of energy.
Alternative energy is not yet able to produce such volumes.
The problem, according to the organizers of the forum, can be solved by nature-like technologies, which are being developed by young scientists.
In addition, Kovalchuk raised the issue of responsibility for the development of nature-like technologies, and also spoke about the risks that inevitably arise when creating such technologies.
"The arrival of such technologies is a unique thing, it's a tremendous asset.
It's the explosion of medical technology, it's the improvement of the quality of life and infrastructure.
But there's a second side.
The development of nature-like technologies is actually the technological reproduction of living nature systems.
There's the reverse side, which is deliberate interference with human life.
There are always risks.
A car came along, and people started dying under the wheels.
But cars are still used.
The dual nature of technology at once.
I'm creating a new medical technology, and at the same time I can create weapons of mass destruction", REN TV quotes the scientist.
After viewing the film and discussing the latest scientific breakthroughs, the students were able to ask questions to the participants.
The role of speakers was played by the candidate of physics and mathematics, the head of the Kurchatov complex of NBIKS-natural technologies of the NIC "Kurchatov Institute" Yulia Dyakova and the head of the Kurchatov complex of NBIKS-technologies Vyacheslav Demin.
The Sirius Education Center in Sochi was created by the "Talent and Success" educational foundation on the basis of the Olympic infrastructure on the initiative of Russian President Vladimir Putin.
The aim of the work of the educational centre is to identify, develop and further support gifted children at an early stage.
Earlier in September, it was reported that the winners of the all-Russian Cyber-Challenge online information security competition would be sent to Sirius for training.
