Peskov responded to a question about Serbia's possible support for Kosovo
Press Secretary of the President of Russia Dmitry Peskov believes that it is too early to say whether Russia will provide assistance to Serbia after the escalation in Kosovo.
He said that first the leaders of the two countries should hold talks.
A Kremlin spokesman told reporters on the radio station "Moscow Speaks" on Sunday, September 30.
On September 29, Serbian resident Alexander Vučić said he intends to discuss the situation in Kosovo with Russian President Vladimir Putin at the upcoming meeting in Moscow on October 2.
The Serbian leader also planned to ask Moscow for support in the current situation, clarifying that military aid was not in question in this case.
Vucic said he would like to preserve peace in the region and intends to do everything necessary for this.
Earlier in the day, it was reported that the president of Serbia had ordered the country's armed forces to be put on high alert.
